Sharper Image Corp said itregistered with the Securities and Exchange Commission to offer1,445,000 shares of its common stock.    The offering would be comprised of 1.2 mln shares of newlyissued stock and 245,000 shares offered by certain sellingshareholders.    Net proceeds would be used to finance the opening of newstores and for working capital.    The offering is scheduled for April and would beunderwritten by a group managed by L.F. Rothschild, Unterberg,Towbin Inc and Dean Witter Reynolds Inc. Reuter&#3;